Micro Bubble Exhaust Valve is a device specially designed to effectively remove tiny bubbles and free gases from the fluid system. Its core working principle relies on the spiral mesh structure inside it; the mesh is welded by copper wire into a three‑dimensional configuration that creates relatively static zones where fluid flow slows, allowing bubbles to detach and collect in an internal air chamber that discharges through an automatic air‑release valve. Because the spiral mesh induces minimal pressure loss, system efficiency remains high while preventing cavitation and flow instability. An auxiliary side valve further removes suspended impurities, enhancing cleanliness and operational stability across applications such as water supply, industrial pump systems, and boiler steam systems.

