What is a Micro Bubble Exhaust Valve?
A Micro Bubble Exhaust Valve is engineered to capture microscopic gas pockets that form during fluid circulation in pipelines and boiler systems. The valve’s spiral mesh configuration creates a low‑velocity micro‑channel where bubbles naturally coalesce and are funneled into an internal chamber. This chamber discharges through an automatically and remotely controllable air‑release valve, thereby preventing bubble accumulation, cavitation, and pressure spikes that can damage downstream equipment. The design ensures negligible pressure drop, preserving the overall energy efficiency of the system while extending the lifespan of pumps, compressors and turbine blades.

